SPEC: https://specifications.freedesktop.org/basedir-spec/latest/

* `XDG_DATA_HOME` user-specific data files
    * default `$HOME/.local/share`
    * if `XDG_DATA_DIRS` exists, it will be a list of items separated by `:`, search these directories if file doesn't exist under `$XDG_DATA_HOME`

* `XDG_CONFIG_HOME` user-specific config files
    * default `$HOME/.config`
    * if `XDG_CONFIG_DIRS` exists, it will be a list of items separated by `:`, search these directories if file doesn't exist under `$XDG_CONFIG_HOME`

* `XDG_STATE_HOME` user-specific state data (including logs?)
    * default `$HOME/.local/state`

* `XDG_CACHE_HOME` user-specific non-essential (cached) data
    * default `$HOME/.cache`

* `XDG_RUNTIME_DIR` user-specific runtime files (sockets, pipes, etc.)
    * no default value
    * must be owned by user, mode 0700
    * create on login, delete on logout, contents MUST NOT survive logout/reboot
    * see docs for more info

$HOME/.local/bin    user-specific binaries, should be included in PATH
